\newlabel{fig:exp_synthetic_transfer_regime_estimation}{{1}{8}{Regime-0 expert dependence in the synthetic transfer experiment. Each heatmap shows the pairwise Pearson correlation (color: \([-1,1]\)) between experts' per-round losses (experts indexed \(0\)--\(3\)). Top row: partial feedback (only queried losses observed). Columns (left-to-right) show the ground-truth correlation implied by the simulator and the correlations estimated by each method. L2D-SLDS best recovers the block-structured correlations (experts \(\{0,1\}\) vs.\ \(\{2,3\}\)). \relax }{figure.caption.1}{}}
\newlabel{fig:exp_synthetic_transfer_regime_estimation@cref}{{[figure][1][]1}{[1][7][]8}}
